"{\"uid\": \"breitbart.com-sports-2024-07-30-activist-center-olympics-last-supper-threatens-legal-action-online-abuse\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A French DJ and LGBTQ activist is taking legal action over online abuse regarding her role in the 2024 Paris Olympics opening ceremony's \\\"Last Supper\\\" display.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9350402361108786, \"rank\": 0.06393815763841332, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbara Butch's attorney, Audrey Msellati, wrote in a statement posted to Butch'sInstagramthat the DJ and activist who played \\\"Christ\\\" in the display had \\\"been the target of an extremely violent campaign of cyber-harassment and defamation.\\\"\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 187, \"end\": 193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9863201162996202, \"rank\": 0.01386961559846066, \"text\": \"Audrey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.999995012920338, \"rank\": 4.979493402702409e-06, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response, Msellati said Butch was \\\"filing several complaints against these acts,\\\" regardless of whether they had been \\\"committed by French nationalists or foreigners.\\\"\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_nationalism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French nationalists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_nationalism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_nationalism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Since the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games, artist, DJ, and activist Barbara Butch has been the target of an extremely violent campaign of cyber-harassment and defamation,\\\" Msellati wrote in the letter.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Msellati explained that Butch was \\\"threatened with death, torture, and rape\\\" and had also \\\"been the target of numerous anti-Semitic, homophobic, sexist and grossophobic insults.\\\"\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\", \"score\": 0.9993573908791704, \"rank\": 0.0006430223329053505, \"text\": \"anti-Semitic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Barbara Butch condemns this vile hatred directed at her, what she represents, and what she stands for,\\\" the letter continues.\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony featured a parody of the \\\"Last Supper\\\" in which Butch was in the middle, while drag queens and transgender performers stood on either side of her.\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the aftermath of the display, the organizers of the Olympics have received criticism.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A spokesperson for the Olympics issued a statement that there was \\\"Never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group\\\" and that the organizers had tried to \\\"celebrate community tolerance.\\\"\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minnesota Bishop Robert Barroncriticizedthe apology, stating that \\\"everyone's tolerated\\\" except for the \\\"2.6 billion Christians on the planet.\\\"\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1563, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999880440664902, \"rank\": 1.1476196808626372e-05, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director for the opening ceremony of the Olympics,explainedduring an interview that the \\\"idea\\\" had been \\\"to do a big pagan party linked to the gods of Olympus,\\\" according to France24.\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1708, \"end\": 1714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9998181028247446, \"rank\": 0.0001792900799488668, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9978625320532681, \"rank\": 0.001797174523612206, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}, {\"begin\": 1909, \"end\": 1917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_24\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"France24\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_24\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_24\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CatholicVote, a conservative, non-profit political advocacy group, has also criticized President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris for their silence on the \\\"Last Supper\\\" parody.\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2017, \"end\": 2020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.7780173934411433, \"rank\": 0.1259239406245549, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 2021, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 0.9999999344920546, \"rank\": 6.550789423354819e-08, \"text\": \"Biden\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\"}, {\"begin\": 2046, \"end\": 2052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.426559052606277e-16, \"text\": \"Kamala\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pleaselet us knowif you are having issues with commenting.\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Breitbart\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2193, \"end\": 2202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999736858175, \"rank\": 2.631409559880765e-08, \"text\": \"Breitbart\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\"}]}]}"